    "Batch size" slider, and the "Show test data" button.
[ ] make the reset button set all the weights to zero.
[ ] make the output's bias editable. currently there are no rectangles we can
    click to edit the bias.
[ ] make it easier to edit the weights and bias by hand: instead of clicking to
    enable the edit box where we need to type the new value for the weight or
    bias, let the user click-and-drag to smoothly adjust the value.
[ ] hit shift while click-and-dragging to snap to the nearest 0.1 increment.
[ ] hit L while hovering over a weight to Lock or Unlock it. Locked weights do
    not display the popup showing the weight. This makes it easier to look at and
    edit the weights of the non-locked weights in the cases in which the wires
    overlap and the mouse hovers several weights at once. Locking takes
    precedence over Unlocking if the mouse hovers over several weights at once.
    Pressing L should only Lock or Unlock a single weight.
